	<body>
		<h1>Coco Curry</h1>
	
		<img src="http://imgur.com/gallery/EhsIH">
		
		<section>
				<h2>Ingredents</h2>
				
					<ul>
				<li>6 Cups Chicken Broth </li>
				<li>3 Tbs. Flour</li>
				<li>5 Tbs. Butter</li>
				<li>3 Tbs. Curry powder</li>
				<li>Chilli powder (to taste)</li>
				<li>1 Tbs. Turmeric</li>
				<li>1 Tbs. Garmin Marsala</li>
				<li>2 Tsp. Cummin</li>
				<li>1 Tsp. Garlic</li>
				<li>1 Lb. Grouned Beef</li>
				<li>2 Slices Mozzarella</li>
				<li>2 Sliced Carrots</li>
				<li>2 Sliced stocks of Celery</li>
				<li>1 Diced Pepper</li>
			</ul>
			
			
		<section>
			<h2>Steps</h2>
				<ol>
					<li>Bring the chicken broth to a boil in a medium sized pot and add the carrots, celery and diced pepper.</li>
					<li>Seperate the grouned beef into four equal parts, placed one slice of mozzarella on two on them. Then take the pattys without mozzarella and put them on top, being sure to cover all of the cheese.</li>
					<li>Melt the butter into a sauce pan,once melted add the flour and wisk until brown.</li>
					<li>Once the flour is browned, lower the heat and wisk in the spices.</li>
					<li>After the spiced are mixed into the flour, add the rue to the pot. Mix in well.</li>
					<li>Put a lid on the pot and let simmer</li<
					<li>Take the two cheese filled burgers you had made and cook them in a pan, add a little oil if they begin to stick.</li>
					<li>Once the burrgers are cooked to taste, put them on a covered plate to the side.</li>
					<li>Finally plate the curry over rice with the burger on top and enjoy</li>
			 </ol>
				 
	
					
	
	</body>
	
	
	
